ty World News site</b></font></a><br><br><span style=3D"font-size: 10pt; co=
lor: #003366"><b>AFRICA: Going where for-profits dare not tread</b></span><=
br><I>Sharon Dell</I><BR>
Exporting online higher education to the African continent is not for the f=
aint of heart. It=92s a complicated and costly affair, which means that for=
-profit operators have tended shy away from it. One university seems to hav=
e cornered the African market in providing distance and online post-school =
education, with the help of some political goodwill at the highest levels o=
f government. The huge University of South Africa, Unisa, has brought a dev=
elopmental vision to Sub-Saharan Africa, embracing the continent and earnin=
g a solid reputation in the process. <br><a href=3D"http://www.universitywo=
rldnews.com/article.php?story=3D20100925161136685" style=3D"font-size: 8pt;=
