rsity World News site</b></font></a><br><br><span style=3D"font-size: 10pt;=
 color: #003366"><b>GLOBAL: Q&A with on-line pioneer John Daniel</b></span>=
<br><I>David Jobbins</I><BR>
Sir John Daniel has been at the leading edge of the open and distance learn=
ing (ODL) movement through his roles as Vice-chancellor of the UK=92s Open =
University, Assistant Director General of UNESCO and, currently, President =
of the Commonwealth of Learning in Vancouver, Canada, an organisation that =
has set the standard for ODL in developing countries. Among the many projec=
ts it supports is Teacher Education in Sub-Saharan Africa, TESSA, whose ope=
n educational materials were used by 300,000 African teachers last year.<br=
